theorem
Th17: (for f being (Function of ( TopSpaceMetr M1 ),( TopSpaceMetr M2 )) holds (f is  continuous iff (for p being (Point of M1) holds (for q being (Point of M2) holds (for r being  positive  real number holds (q = ( f . p ) implies (ex s being  positive  real number st ( f .: ( Ball (p,s) ) ) c= ( Ball (q,r) ))))))))
proof
let f being (Function of ( TopSpaceMetr M1 ),( TopSpaceMetr M2 ));
hereby
assume A1: f is  continuous;
let p being (Point of M1);
let q being (Point of M2);
let r being  positive  real number;
assume that
A2: q = ( f . p );
r in ( REAL ) by XREAL_0:def 1;
then consider s being (Element of ( REAL )) such that A3: s > ( 0 ) and A4: (for w being (Element of M1) holds (for w1 being (Element of M2) holds ((w1 = ( f . w ) & ( dist (p,w) ) < s) implies ( dist (q,w1) ) < r))) by A1,A2,UNIFORM1:4;
reconsider s as  positive  real number by A3;
take s;
thus ( f .: ( Ball (p,s) ) ) c= ( Ball (q,r) )
proof
let y being set;
assume y in ( f .: ( Ball (p,s) ) );
then consider x being (Point of ( TopSpaceMetr M1 )) such that A5: x in ( Ball (p,s) ) and A6: ( f . x ) = y by FUNCT_2:65;
reconsider x1 = x as (Point of M1);
